\section{Other}
\label{sec:org33f3d93}
\begin{itemize}
\item Danforth, Putnam, Parris
\begin{description}
\item[{Danforth}] Motivated by justice, wants to maintain the reputation of the court, accuses Proctor of undermining the court to prevent this. Danforth is a perpetuator of the witch hunt system.
\item[{Putnam}] Motivated by greed, wants to gain land from those that are hanged in witch trials. Putnam is not a perpetuator, but is an active participant and a malicious actor within the system.
\item[{Parris}] Motivated by pride, doesn't want to tarnish his name by having it known that his daughter and neice are liars.
\end{description}
\end{itemize}
